title: Quadrant Chart
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A quadrant chart divides a plane into four sectors defined by two axes and plots labeled points. Use it for prioritization, competitive positioning, risk assessment, or any "high/low × high/low" analysis. ''New in Mermaid 10.3.''

---

!! Basic example

```
quadrantChart
    title Effort vs Value
    x-axis Low Effort --> High Effort
    y-axis Low Value --> High Value
    quadrant-1 Quick Wins
    quadrant-2 Major Projects
    quadrant-3 Low Priority
    quadrant-4 Reconsider
    Task A: [0.2, 0.8]
    Task B: [0.7, 0.9]
    Task C: [0.8, 0.3]
    Task D: [0.3, 0.25]
```

