---

!! Syntax

```
quadrantChart
    title Chart Title
    x-axis Left Label --> Right Label
    y-axis Bottom Label --> Top Label
    quadrant-1 Top-right label
    quadrant-2 Top-left label
    quadrant-3 Bottom-left label
    quadrant-4 Bottom-right label
    Point Name: [x, y]
```

* Coordinates are decimals between 0 and 1 (`[x, y]`).
* Quadrants are numbered: 1 = top-right, 2 = top-left, 3 = bottom-left, 4 = bottom-right.
* Quadrant labels are optional.

!! Tips

* Point names with colons or special characters may need quoting.
* Avoid clustering too many points — label overlap reduces readability.
* Use this for decisions, not for precise data — coordinates are approximate placements.

